images.caption: In-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition of a large Japanese village sprawling from east to west. Slightly above the civilization is a grassy plain with tents, blue units on foot and horseback as well as siege weapons. A thin river can be seen running along the North of the city, separating the city from the tents. Several teal units and blue units can be seen moving about the village. A slightly translucent black banner appears from the lower left of the image to the right. Words over the banner read, "NEW CO-OP MODE!"

In-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition of a large Japanese village sprawling from east to west. An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A large ancient village can be seen with a large stone fortress and several other large stone buildings with turquoise domes ontop of them. To the right of the buildings are patches of trees and farmlands. Along the West and North of the village is deep blue water. Yellow calvary units can be seen just outside of the large stone fortress. Teal units on horseback and foot can be seen traveling through the village. Teal onagers can be seen sitting on the Southern end of the village. A slightly translucent black banner appears from the lower left of the image to the right. Words over the banner read, "NEW CO-OP MODE!"

A fall in-game scene from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A large village can be seen from the center of the image to the lower left corner of the image. There are large stone buildings with red roofs and the largest stone building has a large golden dome. Patches of trees with golden yellow, green, and red leaves, appear throughout. To the right of the village is a river and waterfall. A stone bridge crosses from west to east, going past the waterfall. There is a large mass of blue units at the west end of the stone bridge. To the south of the village is a large stone gate with green horseback units traveling along a stone path. Several green units can be seen throughout the village. To the north is a raiding blue army attacking the village's stone walls. Some of the stone walls are alit.

A large stone wall and gate can be seen north-east of the windmills. There are red units travelling along a dirt path along the north-west to the gate.

A lush green in-game scene is shown from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A large village is filled with large stone buildings, a large religious statue of a person sitting cross-legged, and several blue units on foot as well as on elephant. There is a tall temple at the center with a gold dome at the top. There is a large stone castle at the top-center of the image surrounded by units on elephants. The village is framed by a turquoise body of water to the north, east, and south. A large forested area is to the north-west.

An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A large we-developed village can be seen. Large stone buildings cover the land, each highlighted by a strip of red. At the center of the village is a monastery. The roof tops of each building are covered in a reddish brown material. The village is framed by a large stone wall, green trees, and a large body of water. The village is bustling with many red units on foot and on horseback. To the north west of the village is a stone gate leading to a stone bridge.

An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A large body of turquoise water can be see with a large marine battle occurring. The ships battle long the shore of a piece of land in the lower right corner of the image. Along the shore is a dock with fishing boats, several teal units on horseback and on elephants, and a large stone castle with golden trip on the top. The castle is surrounded by patches of grass and a stone bridge to the far right. There are several ships on fire or blown to pieces. Debris is scattered across the water.

In-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition of a large ancient village with large stone buildings, including a stone monastery in the upper right corner. There are several red units throughout the village, including mangonels and scorpions. All of the buildings are surrounded by a tall stone wall on the southern end. The wall and buildings all have reddish brown rooftops. There is a gate on the southern wall that is on fire. Bright blue water is south of the village with a long stone bridge. Red cavalry units are battling blue cavalry units on the bridge, near the gate. Blue siege units can be seen attacking the gate.  South east of the bridge are additional buildings surrounded by blue calvary units and trebuchets.

South east of the bridge are additional buildings surrounded by blue calvary units and trebuchets.

In-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. A desert scene is shown. A growing village surrounded by sand, patches of grass, and several farms. A few patches of trees, such as palm trees, appear about the tranquil scene. The village is surrounded by walls and is bustling with purple units on camels as well as units on foot. Ostriches, and other wildlife, are to the south east of the village.

An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive edition showcasing a sprawling ancient city marked with highlights of green and filled with large stone buildings. A monastery is in the center of the city and just north of it is a large stone castle marked with highlights of purple. To the right of the castle is a tall windmill surrounded by lush green trees. There are several purple troops standing just south of the castle, in a town square that has a tall statue at its' center.

An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive edition showcasing a sprawling ancient city marked with highlights of green and filled with large stone buildings. An in-game screenshot from Age of Empires II: Definitive Edition. There is an ancient civilization with a few large stone buildings, several with blue domes ontop. The buildings are surrounded by a large stone wall, with a gate on the north west side and one on the north east side. A large army of yellow trimmed units, many on horseback, are gathered inside. A large purple army, consisting of calvary and siege weapons, is charging both northern gates. A long blue river runs along the south with a stone bridge connecting the civilization to the land beyond.
